parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: ABS Light Illumination and Intermittent Brake Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the brake system can cause extended stopping distances, accidents, or leave the driver stranded.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear brake cylinder can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to extended stopping distances and accidents.
symptoms: stuck or frozen rear brake pistons
rear brake calipers and rotors need to be replaced frequently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake rotors can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to extended stopping distances and accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the speed sensor can cause the ABS light to illuminate, leading to intermittent brake failure and extended stopping distances.
symptoms: speed sensor failure diagnosed by computer diagnostics.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Power Steering Rack and Pinion Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering rack and pinion can cause loss of steering control, making it difficult or impossible to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: clicking noises when turning the wheel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the lower pinion bearing can cause loss of steering control, making it difficult or impossible to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.

The failure to honor the recall can lead to continued use of a faulty power steering rack and pinion, which can cause loss of steering control, making it difficult or impossible to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: faulty power steering rack and pinion not replaced.

and smoke coming from underneath the dash.
